news.title: Benefits under PMAY-G provided to deceased persons, ineligible ones: Auditors find in Bihar
news.para: ​Unrealistic geo-tagging of house locations and payment of instalments in wrong accounts are also among the discrepancies observed by teams of the accountant general (AG-Bihar) during the audit of the implementation of the rural housing scheme in the state.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Appeal against society's redevelopment junked
news.para: The bench headed by Chief Justice Sunita Agarwal turned down an appeal filed by 15 members of the society, who were opposing the redevelopment scheme on different grounds.

news.title: Minor building plan changes to be regularised by civic bodies in West Bengal
news.para: As per the notification, a deviation from the sanctioned linear dimensions of parts of a building up to 5%, without change in the internal arrangements, will be considered minor deviation.

news.title: DVAC to probe PMAY fund scam, Tamil Nadu government informs Madras HC
news.para: The court was hearing a contempt petition by K Udhayakumar who had filed a public interest litigation earlier complaining about the alleged fund misappropriation by Lalgudi panchayat union officials.

news.title: Pune civic body razes 1.5 lakh sq ft of illegal constructions in green belt
news.para: PMC officials said the administration also removed around 6,000 cubic feet of sand, which was used for reclamation near the riverbank. The sand was transported to Wagholi quarry using six dumpers.

news.title: Only 5% of residential buildings have occupancy certificates: Ranchi civic body
news.para: Out of the 2,451 building plans that were approved by the RMC between 2020 and 2023, only 173 applications for the mandatory occupancy certificates have been received from the builders.

news.title: 'Buildings can fall anytime,' Signature View Apartments RWA tells DDA
news.para: The apartment complex in Mukherjee Nagar, built in 2007-09 with 336 MIG and HIG flats, has some construction issues and is up for demolition by the Delhi Development Authority.

news.title: Adani Group to invest over Rs 1,700 crore to expand cement business in Uttarakhand
news.para: "In the cement sector, we will invest in excess of Rs 1,700 crore to expand Ambuja Cements' existing capacity in Uttarakhand," group director Pranav Adani said said.

news.title: In a first, Mivan technology to be used for PMAY homes in Udham Singh Nagar
news.para: ​The technique, used for the first time in government schemes in the state, eliminates the need for traditional bricks and reduces labour requirements.

news.title: Bank of Canada urges removal of barriers to home building to cut inflation
news.para: Deputy governor Toni Gravelle spoke a day after the central bank held its key overnight rate at 5% but left the door open to another hike, saying it was still concerned about inflation.

news.title: Karnataka government tables bill in assembly proposing hike in stamp duty
news.para: ​The bill titled The Karnataka Stamp (Amendment) Bill, 2023 was tabled in the Assembly by Rural Development Minister Priyank Kharge on behalf of Revenue Minister Krishna Byre Gowda.

news.title: China: Shimao Group trades flat after issuing plan to revamp offshore debt
news.para: Shimao Group, with around $11.7 billion in offshore notes, bonds and other credit facilities has been pushing forward plans to revamp its debts over the past few months, Shimao said in a filing to the Hong Kong Stock Exchange late on Thursday.

news.title: RBI retains repo rate at 6.5% for fifth time in a row
news.para: Announcing the bi-monthly monetary policy, RBI Governor Shaktikanta Das said the Monetary Policy Committee (MPC) unanimously decided to keep the repo rate unchanged at 6.5 per cent.

news.title: Prayagraj civic body issues 'red notice' to over 7,000 house tax defaulters
news.para: Of these, 2,433 have an outstanding of more than Rs 1 lakh. If these defaulters fail to deposit the dues within a given time, action will be taken to attach and seal their building. There are a total of 2.32 lakh buildings in the municipal corporation (except extended areas).

news.title: Land identified for Tidel park in Nilgiris: Tamil Nadu tourism minister
news.para: After inspecting the site, the minister said that a proposal in this regard would soon be sent to the government. The setting up of a Tidel park in the Nilgiris was one of the election promises made by the DMK.

news.title: Goa: GIDC notifies revised plot allotment regulations to attract new investment
news.para: The new norms have introduced a marking system for plot allotment, which gives additional points for women entrepreneurs, local entrepreneurs, start-ups, patent holders and sustainability measures.

news.title: Has Bengaluru development body lost the plot on Kempegowda Layout story?
news.para: BDA fails to provide basic amenities at one of its well-known layouts, misses 4 deadlines and now stands accused of having provided wrong info in Assembly
